Citation.sTitle: Isobaric vapor-liquid equilibrium data of the binary systems of octane with p, o, m-xylene at 20 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) data were determined at 20 kPa for the three binary mixtures composed of octane + p, o, m-xylene by using a recirculation type still. All the data passed the thermodynamics  test and no azeotropic behavior was observed. The experimental results were used as a basis to  check the validity of two predictive models, the UNIFAC (DORTMUND) and COSMO-RS. These new VLE data were also correlated with the Wilson, NRTL, and UNIQUAC activity coefficient models.
